    <title> CheckPoint: Angular Collision </title>
    <p>The diagram shows the side view of two uniform solid discs spinning in the same direction on a horizontal thin frictionless axle. The discs are made of the same material that has the same thickness. The disc on the right has twice the radius of the disc on the left. The angular speeds of the discs are 2&#x3C9; and &#x3C9;, respectively. 
</p><br/>
